_meanings:
{@--1@} To be red;  
{#BfSamanvarajyadatuzArakaraH#} <ls>Śi. 9. 7</ls> (became red
or attached).

{@--2@} To be delighted, find
pleasure; {#tava prakIrtyA#} 
{#jagatprahfzyatyanurajyate ca#} <ls>Bg. 11. 36.</ls>

{@--3@} To be 
attached or devoted to, be fond of,
love, like (with <ab>acc.</ab> or <ab>loc.</ab>);  
{#samasTamanurajyaMti vizamasTaM tyajaMti ca#} <ls>Rām.</ls>;
{#aSudDaprakftO rAjYi janatA nAnurajyate#}  
<ls>Pt. 1. 301</ls>; {#BrAturmftasya BAryAyAM yo'nurajyeta#}
{#kAmataH#} <ls>Ms. 3. 173.</ls>

{@--2@} To attach oneself to, please,
gratify, conciliate, keep contented
or satisfied; {#anuraktaH prajABiSca#} 
{#prajAScApyanvaraMjayat#} <ls>Rām.</ls>; {#kaMzwaM janaH#} 
{#kulaDanEranuraMjanIyaH#} <ls>U. 1. 14</ls>;  
{#SizyaguRAnurAMjitamanasaM#} <ls>Pt. 1</ls> pleased, gratified.
